cs.GT, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.IT 

The paper deals with game theory and information theory in the context of a mobile social network application. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics). The paper also involves machine learning algorithms, which suggests the category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper discusses the accuracy of the learning algorithm, which could fall under the category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the analysis of a model with stochastic paths, which could fall under the category cs.CY (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper involves information restriction mechanisms, which could fall under the category cs.IT (Information Theory).
